        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The “Nariwal Paudha Vitaran Yojana”, launched by the Department of Agriculture, Bihar, is designed to distribute coconut saplings to farmers and individuals willing to plant on their land. The main objective of this scheme is to plant coconut saplings in non-traditional coconut areas in the state.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **Subsidy Support:** 75% subsidy i.e. ₹63.75/- will be payable on the unit cost of ₹85/- per sapling.  - **Distribution of Saplings:** A minimum of 5 and a maximum of 712 saplings (178 saplings per hectare) will be provided to beneficiaries.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aimed at promoting coconut cultivation in non-traditional areas like Bihar. Under this scheme, farmers and urban residents can obtain coconut saplings at a subsidized rate to encourage widespread plantation and utilization.\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
